<article class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5">
    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Many business owners focus on getting new attention, but forget to follow up with people who already know them. Email marketing helps you stay connected with customers, leads, and past buyers.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Email supports the rest of your marketing</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Your website, ads, content marketing, and social media marketing can bring people in. Email helps continue the conversation after they leave your site or profile.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">What should small businesses send?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-5">Strong email marketing campaigns are useful, not spammy. Good ideas include:</p>
      <ul class="checklist mb-8">
        <li>Seasonal promotions and limited-time offers.</li>
        <li>Helpful tips related to your service.</li>
        <li>Reminders for appointments, maintenance, or renewals.</li>
        <li>New service announcements.</li>
        <li>Customer stories and before-and-after examples.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">When to hire an email marketing company</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">An email marketing company can help when you need list setup, templates, campaign planning, automations, and reporting. The goal is to send the right message to the right people at the right time.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Keep it simple at first</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">You do not need a complicated email strategy. Start with a welcome message, monthly useful email, and occasional offer. As your list grows, add segmentation and automation.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Email works best as part of a complete <a href="/en/blog/internet-marketing-services-small-business/" style="color:var(--primary)">internet marketing services</a> plan with local SEO, social media, content, and paid advertising.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
